                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <h2 class="headings">&#126; About &#126;</h2>
                    <p class="content">Seth M.R. Jaipuria Schools is a group of schools run by the Seth M.R. Jaipuria
                        Group.
                        The schools
                        draw their name from 1971 Padma Bhushan awardee Mungtu Ram Jaipuria, a philanthropist and
                        industrialist who played a dominant role in the industrialization of the nation after
                        independence.Seth M.R. Jaipuria School, New Delhi is affiliated to the Indian Council for
                        Secondary
                        Examinations, New Delhi.The school imparts education from the Pre-Primary level to class XII. In
                        classes XI the school offers three potential streams i.e. Science, Commerce and Humanities.It
                        aims
                        at the all round development of the
                        child and strives to mould them into sincere, dedicated, distinguished and morally sound
                        citizens of
                        the country.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-6 ">
                    <h2 class="headings">&#126; Infrastructure &#126;</h2>
                    <p class="content">The school campus consists of three buildings
                        with spacious, well- ventilated classrooms, libraries and well equipped laboratories. It has
                        well
                        maintained playground. The school imparts education from the Pre-Primary level to class XII. In
                        classes XI the school offers three potential streams i.e. Science, Commerce and Humanities.It
                        aims
                        at the all round development of the
                        child and strives to mould them into sincere, dedicated, distinguished and morally sound
                        citizens of
                        the country. </p>
                </div>
